Honors | Amir M. Rahmani Amir M. Rahmani Marie Curie Global Fellow at UC Irvine, USA & TU Wien, Austria Docent at UTU, Finland About Publications Projects Teaching Students Professional Services Honors Contact Honors Best Paper Award from Elsevier International Conference on Ambient Systems, Networks and Technologies, 2019. HiPEAC (European Network on High Performance and Embedded Architecture and Compilation) Paper Awards for our ASPLOS'18 paper, 2018. HiPEAC (European Network on High Performance and Embedded Architecture and Compilation) Paper Awards for our DAC'18 paper, 2018. Best Paper Award from International Conference on Wireless Mobile Communication and Healthcare (MobiHealth), 2017. IEEE Senior Member. Life-time Docent title awarded by the Rector of University of Turku, Finland, 2016. Global Marie Curie Fellowship awarded by the European Union (EU) with the score of 94.5% (success rate EU-wide < 10%), 2016. Nominee for "The Teacher of the Year" at University of Turku, chosen by students (university-wide), 2016. Rank 10 by number of publications at University of Turku (among 544 authors in the field of engineering) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to Elsevier SciVal. Rank 10 by number of publications at University of Turku (among 544 authors in the field of computer science) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to Elsevier SciVal. Rank 52 by number of publications at University of Turku (among 4893 authors in all subject areas) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to Elsevier SciVal. Best Paper Award from International Conference on IoT Technologies for Health Care, 2015. Best Paper Candidate in 25th IEEE DFT Symposium, 2015. Ulla Tuominen Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2012. Best Student Paper Award from IEEE International Symposium on Defect and Fault Tolerance in VLSI and Nanotechnology Systems (DFT) Sponsored by Intel Corporation, 2011. Nokia Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2011. Nokia Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2010. Iran Telecommunication Research Center (ITRC) Research Excellence Award, 2007.